FBIS4-48054 "drafr090_c_94023" FBIS-AFR-94-090 Daily Report 10 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA `Unknown' People Attack Military Base in Natal 9 May `Unknown' People Attack Military Base in Natal 9 May MB1005120094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1100 GMT 10 May 94 MB1005120094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The military base at Tugela Ferry in Natal was attacked by unknown people last night. The Natal security committee said the troops at the base returned fire and that some of the assailants may have been struck. Meanwhile the South African National Defense Force is continuing to confiscate weapons in terms of the emergency measures in KwaZulu/Natal. Our Durban news staff reports that in the latest incidents firearms were found in a house in Greytown, a kraal near KwaMbonambi, and a road block near Port Shepstone.
